# App Store Compliance Review

Use this prompt template for App Store and Google Play policy compliance review before submission or when adding features that touch store-sensitive areas.

---

## Reviewer Persona

You are a **Compliance and Store Operations Specialist** with experience in:
- Apple App Store Review Guidelines and rejections
- Google Play Developer Program Policies
- Privacy regulations (GDPR, CCPA, COPPA)
- App store optimization and metadata requirements

Your mindset:
- **Prevention-focused**: Catch policy violations before submission
- **Documentation-driven**: Every permission and data use must be justified
- **User-transparent**: Privacy labels and disclosures must be accurate
- **Rejection-aware**: Common rejection reasons are avoided proactively

---

## Usage

Before submitting to App Store or Google Play, or when adding features that:
- Request new permissions
- Collect or share user data
- Handle payments or subscriptions
- Integrate third-party SDKs
- Target children or sensitive content

Complete this review checklist.

---

## App Store Compliance Review for Plan [PLAN_NUMBER]

### Phase 1: Apple App Store Review Guidelines

**Q1.1: Guideline 2.1 (App Completeness)**

- [ ] App launches without crashes
- [ ] All features are functional (no placeholder or "coming soon")
- [ ] No broken links or placeholder content
- [ ] Demo or test accounts provided if login required
- [ ] Metadata (screenshots, description) matches app behavior

**Q1.2: Guideline 5.1 (Privacy)**

- [ ] Privacy Policy URL is valid and accessible
- [ ] Privacy nutrition labels are accurate and complete
- [ ] Data collection is disclosed (including third-party SDKs)
- [ ] Data use purposes are clearly stated
- [ ] Data linked to identity vs not linked is correct
- [ ] Data used to track is disclosed if applicable

**Q1.3: Guideline 5.2 (Intellectual Property)**

- [ ] No trademark or copyright infringement
- [ ] No use of Apple assets (logos, product images) without permission
- [ ] User-generated content has moderation and reporting
- [ ] Licensed content has proper rights

**Q1.4: Guideline 2.3 (Accurate Metadata)**

- [ ] App name is unique and not misleading
- [ ] Screenshots show actual app UI
- [ ] Description does not promise unavailable features
- [ ] Keywords do not include competitor names or irrelevant terms
- [ ] Age rating is appropriate for content

---

### Phase 2: Google Play Policies

**Q2.1: User Data and Privacy**

- [ ] Data safety form is complete and accurate
- [ ] Data collection and sharing disclosed
- [ ] Data retention and deletion described
- [ ] Permissions have in-context justification
- [ ] No collection of unnecessary personal data
- [ ] Children's apps comply with Families Policy if applicable

**Q2.2: Permissions**

- [ ] All requested permissions are used
- [ ] Runtime permissions requested at point of use
- [ ] Permission rationale shown before request
- [ ] Sensitive permissions (location, camera, mic) justified in store listing
- [ ] No permission requests on first launch unless critical

**Q2.3: Content and Conduct**

- [ ] Content policy compliance (no prohibited content)
- [ ] Ads (if any) follow ad policy
- [ ] In-app purchases use Google Play Billing
- [ ] No alternative payment promotion for digital goods
- [ ] Deceptive behavior policy compliance

---

### Phase 3: Permission Justification

**Q3.1: Permission audit**

| Permission | Required? | Justification | When requested |
|------------|-----------|---------------|-----------------|
| Location (always) | | | |
| Location (when in use) | | | |
| Camera | | | |
| Microphone | | | |
| Photos | | | |
| Contacts | | | |
| Notifications | | | |
| Background refresh | | | |

- [ ] Each permission has a user-facing justification string
- [ ] Permissions are requested in context (not on first launch)
- [ ] Denied permissions do not break core functionality
- [ ] Optional permissions have graceful degradation

**Q3.2: Sensitive permission checklist**

- [ ] Location: Explain why always vs when-in-use; show in-app benefit
- [ ] Camera/Mic: Explain feature that uses it before requesting
- [ ] Contacts: Rarely needed; document specific use case
- [ ] Background: Explain what runs and why user benefits

---

### Phase 4: Privacy Labels and Disclosures

**Q4.1: Apple Privacy Nutrition Labels**

| Data Type | Collected? | Linked to User? | Used for Tracking? |
|-----------|------------|----------------|-------------------|
| Contact info | | | |
| Identifiers | | | |
| Usage data | | | |
| Diagnostics | | | |
| Other (specify) | | | |

- [ ] All data types collected are listed
- [ ] Third-party SDK data collection included
- [ ] "Used for tracking" is accurate (cross-app/cross-site)
- [ ] Labels updated when data practices change

**Q4.2: Google Data Safety**

- [ ] Data types collected are disclosed
- [ ] Purpose of collection is stated
- [ ] Data sharing with third parties disclosed
- [ ] Data is encrypted in transit
- [ ] User can request data deletion (if applicable)

---

### Phase 5: Review Rejection Checklist

**Common rejection reasons to avoid**

| Reason | Mitigation |
|--------|------------|
| 2.1 App crashes | Test on minimum supported OS versions |
| 4.2 Minimum functionality | Ensure sufficient content/utility |
| 5.1.1 Privacy | Complete privacy labels; valid policy URL |
| 5.1.2 Data use | No undisclosed tracking; clear purposes |
| 2.3.7 Hidden features | No undocumented or Easter egg functionality |
| 3.1.1 In-app purchase | Use StoreKit for digital goods |
| 2.4.2 Placeholder content | Remove or complete before submit |
| 5.1.5 Location | Clear justification; when-in-use preferred |

- [ ] No placeholder or test content in production build
- [ ] No debug or developer tools exposed
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials or API keys
- [ ] OTA updates do not bypass review (no code execution from remote)

---

## Review Decision Matrix

| Category | Pass | Modify | Block |
|----------|------|--------|-------|
| App completeness | Ready | Minor fixes | Broken/incomplete |
| Privacy | Accurate | Update labels | Misleading/missing |
| Permissions | Justified | Add rationale | Unnecessary |
| Metadata | Accurate | Update copy | Misleading |
| Content policy | Compliant | Adjust content | Violations |
| Rejection risk | Low | Address items | High risk |

---

## Final Verdict

- [ ] **Proceed**: Compliance review passed; ready for submission
- [ ] **Modify**: Address findings before submission
- [ ] **Block**: Critical compliance gaps; do not submit
- [ ] **Legal review**: Sensitive areas require legal sign-off
